WEBVTT

00:10.552 --> 00:12.221
ZACH: Happy birthday.
[Zoe gasps]

00:12.721 --> 00:15.432
HEATHER: I heard a noise.
ZOE: Yeah, I guess
I was just talking to myself.

00:15.432 --> 00:17.851
LARS: Okay. Was it just me
or did anybody else

00:17.851 --> 00:19.770
dream a tad more vividly last night?

00:19.770 --> 00:22.105
‐ Whatever is in these, Dee,
keep 'em coming.

00:22.105 --> 00:24.483
‐ I'm not gonna make it.
‐ You're not gonna make it where?

00:24.483 --> 00:25.692
‐ To the end of the week

00:25.692 --> 00:28.654
The end of the year.
‐ Don't you look at me like‐‐ like‐‐

00:28.654 --> 00:30.906
don't stare at me
like I'm a fucking psycho.

00:30.906 --> 00:34.910
‐ We are on the precipice
of something great.

00:34.910 --> 00:36.912
Stay with me. Stay together.

00:36.912 --> 00:40.999
‐ Mom! Mom!
[gasps and screams]

01:00.143 --> 01:05.524
‐ ♪ You've got this
Strange effect on me ♪

02:28.190 --> 02:29.233
‐ Mmm.

03:24.913 --> 03:26.373
‐ Who are you? What did you‐‐

03:26.373 --> 03:28.208
‐ ♪ Money, money, money
Money, money, money ♪

03:30.002 --> 03:33.380
Can you believe you gave me $128,000?

03:34.089 --> 03:36.466
Ooh! I bet you feel dumb.

03:40.095 --> 03:41.054
‐ Shit.

03:57.988 --> 03:59.573
Son of a‐‐

04:17.633 --> 04:21.011
[Frances scoffs]
PAUL: Ari was never my son.

04:21.762 --> 04:23.430
He's my cousin's son.

04:32.856 --> 04:35.067
‐ You're a small man, Paul Drabble.

04:35.609 --> 04:37.694
‐ ♪ Money, money, money
Money, money, money ♪

04:55.879 --> 04:57.047
BOY: Faggot.
[Young Lars gasps]

05:01.718 --> 05:04.429
‐ What did you call me?
‐ He said faggot.

05:04.847 --> 05:06.557
ALL: Faggot, faggot!

05:06.557 --> 05:09.893
Faggot, faggot!
Faggot, faggot!

05:09.893 --> 05:11.478
Faggot, faggot!

05:11.478 --> 05:15.691
Faggot, faggot!
Faggot, faggot, faggot!

05:15.691 --> 05:20.362
[gasps and breathes heavily]
MASHA: Shh.

05:20.362 --> 05:22.239
‐ What are you doing here?

05:22.239 --> 05:24.241
‐ I hate bullies.

05:25.784 --> 05:27.911
‐ How do you know what I was dreaming?

05:27.911 --> 05:31.665
MASHA: I use a little
auditory subliminal stimuli.

05:31.665 --> 05:34.251
I put in a chemical catalyst, and...

05:34.877 --> 05:38.213
I can see your past trauma with bullies.

05:38.755 --> 05:41.049
‐ What exactly are you giving me?

05:41.049 --> 05:44.469
‐ What I'm giving you is a story.

05:44.469 --> 05:46.680
This is going to be yours.

05:46.680 --> 05:48.140
It's not connected to the internet,

05:48.140 --> 05:49.892
but the camera is working just fine.

05:49.892 --> 05:52.853
So I want you to document
all of the events

05:52.853 --> 05:54.855
that you see today.
I want you to record them,

05:54.855 --> 05:58.275
to write them down.
I want you to do it all.

05:59.651 --> 06:02.362
‐ Why? What's about to happen?
[Masha sighs]

06:02.362 --> 06:03.864
‐ Well for starters...

06:04.573 --> 06:07.409
You are about to happen.

06:07.409 --> 06:10.162
Your whole life
has been about tearing down.

06:10.162 --> 06:12.206
You target the bullies.

06:12.206 --> 06:13.540
Destroy them.

06:14.082 --> 06:15.751
The question is...

06:17.044 --> 06:19.505
have you ever nurtured anything?

06:21.048 --> 06:23.050
‐ No.
‐ No.

06:24.218 --> 06:26.512
Have you ever been a vehicle for growth?

06:27.804 --> 06:28.847
‐ No.

06:29.515 --> 06:32.768
‐ I am gonna offer you
the chance to build something.

06:34.603 --> 06:37.648
Something extraordinary.

06:38.649 --> 06:39.566
So...

06:40.484 --> 06:43.570
you came here to boost your career.

06:44.780 --> 06:49.826
Instead, you get a legacy,
you get the chance

06:49.826 --> 06:53.330
to be the one who told the world.

07:15.644 --> 07:18.397
‐ Wait. So, what do you mean,
she controlled your dream?

07:19.439 --> 07:21.775
‐ I've heard of it
being done with hypnosis.

07:22.568 --> 07:24.778
She does it with drugs and audio.

07:25.237 --> 07:27.281
Like brain entrainment.

07:27.281 --> 07:29.366
‐ So she knew you'd be having a butt baby?

07:29.950 --> 07:31.743
‐ I'm sorry. Was I talking to you?

07:31.743 --> 07:33.620
‐ No, but you were talking loud enough

07:33.620 --> 07:35.205
that I could overhear your conversation.

07:35.205 --> 07:37.249
And by the way, it's my baby too, Lars.

07:37.833 --> 07:38.834
I know my rights.

07:38.834 --> 07:41.670
‐ Okay. Let's not be the Bickersons today.

07:41.670 --> 07:43.505
We had this lovely party last night.

07:43.505 --> 07:47.092
You know, we‐‐ We all sang and danced.

07:47.759 --> 07:50.220
‐ Hi, good morning.
ZOE: Good morning.

07:50.220 --> 07:52.639
‐ So, what'd I miss?
TONY: Oh, apparently

07:52.639 --> 07:55.309
Masha's been manipulating Lars' dreams

07:55.309 --> 07:57.019
with mind control or something.

07:57.019 --> 07:59.062
‐ Drugs and entrainment.
TONY: Whatever.

07:59.062 --> 08:00.898
FRANCES: She's controlling our dreams now?

08:00.898 --> 08:03.567
That explains a lot.
‐ Why, what happened?

08:04.484 --> 08:05.569
MASHA: Hello, everybody.

08:06.737 --> 08:09.323
How are you all doing this morning?

08:09.323 --> 08:12.618
‐ Uh, not‐‐ not great. I‐‐
I'm not sure what you're doing,

08:12.618 --> 08:14.369
dosage‐wise,

08:14.369 --> 08:16.580
but I had some kind of hallucination

08:16.580 --> 08:19.625
or dream last night where Paul Drabble

08:19.625 --> 08:21.126
was like the size of a, you know,

08:21.126 --> 08:22.711
like a garden gnome.
‐ Oh.

08:22.711 --> 08:26.089
FRANCES: I know it's maybe offensive
to talk about someone's size,

08:26.089 --> 08:28.008
but he's an offensive, tiny little man.

08:28.008 --> 08:31.637
So he‐‐ it's fine.
‐ What was he doing?

08:31.637 --> 08:33.889
‐ He was singing a song from Cabaret.

08:33.889 --> 08:35.516
‐ ♪ Willkommen, Bienvenue‐‐ ♪

08:35.516 --> 08:37.309
‐ No, not that one. The‐‐

08:37.309 --> 08:39.186
‐ ♪ Maybe this time I'll be lucky ♪

08:39.186 --> 08:40.687
♪ Maybe this time, maybe‐‐ ♪
FRANCES: No.

08:40.687 --> 08:42.940
I don't even know that one.
The, um‐‐ uh, it was‐‐

08:42.940 --> 08:44.441
‐ ♪ Money, money, money... ♪
FRANCES: Yes, "Money." "Money."

08:44.441 --> 08:45.859
He was singing, "Money, money, money,"

08:45.859 --> 08:48.862
across the floor, by my bed, and then...

08:49.446 --> 08:51.573
inside my toilet.

08:51.573 --> 08:53.617
And I mean, I did not come here

08:53.617 --> 08:56.703
to have a Lilliputian‐sized
internet hustler

08:56.703 --> 08:59.039
sing show tunes to me from the toilet.

08:59.331 --> 09:02.292
‐ That must've been terrifying.
‐ Well, it wasn't a good show.

09:02.292 --> 09:03.710
[laughter]
TONY: Yeah.

09:04.753 --> 09:06.505
‐ How did the dream end?

09:06.964 --> 09:09.341
‐ I‐‐ I flushed him down the toilet.

09:10.551 --> 09:12.261
MASHA:
Now, if I had told you from the start

09:12.261 --> 09:15.180
that you will gonna flush Paul Drabble
down the toilet, what would have you done?

09:15.180 --> 09:16.139
‐ I would have paid you double.

09:18.183 --> 09:21.728
‐ We are all experiencing new things here.

09:23.689 --> 09:27.860
Zoe. Zoe beautifully expressed
her sense of family to you last night.

09:28.402 --> 09:31.154
Ben, Jessica rediscovering each other.

09:31.154 --> 09:33.407
Tony. How about you?

09:33.407 --> 09:35.909
What were you feeling?
It looked like tenderness.

09:37.077 --> 09:40.330
You are okay being a little vulnerable?

09:40.873 --> 09:42.291
‐ No. I'm okay.

09:44.084 --> 09:45.544
‐ So we're making progress here.

09:45.544 --> 09:48.255
And now we are gonna build
on that progress.

09:48.255 --> 09:50.048
We have a slightly higher dose.

09:50.465 --> 09:51.842
I mean, you don't have to take it,

09:51.842 --> 09:53.468
it is up to you, but if you do,

09:53.468 --> 09:55.262
there's a couple more rules,

09:55.262 --> 09:57.222
no climbing, no going near water.

09:57.222 --> 09:59.099
We will also employ the buddy system.

09:59.099 --> 10:01.351
So the Marconis, Ben and Jessica,

10:01.351 --> 10:03.729
Carmel, Lars, and Tony, Frances.

10:03.729 --> 10:05.480
‐ Love it.
MASHA: It's your choice,

10:06.481 --> 10:07.608
but it is safe.

10:08.275 --> 10:09.902
‐ Sounds safe to me.

10:09.902 --> 10:12.154
‐ Cheers?
‐ L'chaim.

10:12.905 --> 10:13.947
‐ Hey, buddy.

10:14.406 --> 10:15.949
‐ Here's mud in your eye.

10:17.159 --> 10:18.493
Mm.
BEN: Down it.

10:18.493 --> 10:20.537
‐ Et tu, Brute?

10:22.122 --> 10:24.041
And then fall Napoleon.

10:25.167 --> 10:27.044
MASHA: It's gonna be a glorious day.

10:36.178 --> 10:37.429
‐ Masha?

10:37.930 --> 10:40.766
Uh, can I see you in private?

10:41.016 --> 10:43.685
My concern is about how this psychedelic

10:43.685 --> 10:47.523
might affect or react, you know,
with other medications.

10:48.690 --> 10:51.193
I'm on a few psychotropics.

10:51.193 --> 10:54.196
Um, I was afraid,

10:54.196 --> 10:56.490
um, I might not be accepted here
if you knew.

10:56.490 --> 10:57.866
So I didn't‐‐
MASHA: Yes.

10:57.866 --> 10:59.993
You're on psychotropics, we know this.

10:59.993 --> 11:01.537
We did your blood work.

11:01.537 --> 11:02.913
It's all right. You're fine.

11:02.913 --> 11:05.958
Nothing to worry about.
‐ [sighs] Okay.

11:06.917 --> 11:09.169
Well, good. Thank you so much.

11:12.506 --> 11:15.926
‐ But I am gonna need
to tell you something, um...

11:17.261 --> 11:20.764
so we can move forward to the next step.

11:25.894 --> 11:27.187
I know...

11:28.689 --> 11:30.315
I know why you came here.

11:32.860 --> 11:35.487
‐ I'm sorry?
‐ It wasn't a coincidence.

11:35.821 --> 11:41.243
You came to a retreat,
this retreat, because...

11:44.288 --> 11:46.248
I had an affair with your husband.

11:49.251 --> 11:51.628
‐ Oh my God, am I in trouble?
‐ No.

11:51.628 --> 11:54.298
‐ I'm in trouble.
‐ No. Of course,
you're not in trouble.

11:54.298 --> 11:55.883
I mean, unless you're trying to kill me.

11:58.177 --> 11:59.386
‐ What?
MASHA: Are you?

11:59.386 --> 12:01.805
Somebody is sending me nasty threats.

12:02.764 --> 12:04.600
Somebody wants to scare me.

12:05.934 --> 12:10.397
‐ Really? Not‐‐ no, it's not me.
I‐‐ I came here to know you.

12:10.814 --> 12:13.817
To see what he saw, to‐‐

12:14.401 --> 12:18.113
to see the‐‐ the what and the‐‐ the why.

12:18.488 --> 12:19.698
The why...

12:23.035 --> 12:24.119
MASHA: Finish that.

12:25.287 --> 12:27.414
‐ Well, it's just that you‐‐ [chuckles]

12:27.414 --> 12:29.166
You were the catalyst for it all.

12:29.166 --> 12:30.542
You‐‐ You...

12:31.752 --> 12:35.339
opened his mind to the idea
that there were beautiful girls

12:35.339 --> 12:36.632
out there to be had...

12:37.925 --> 12:41.345
including the pretty
little bimbo he's with now.

12:44.515 --> 12:46.433
Did you know we were in love, Masha?

12:47.851 --> 12:50.729
Masha, he was crazy about me.

12:50.729 --> 12:53.273
We were‐‐ we were in love.

12:53.774 --> 12:56.026
‐ So you came here to confront me?

12:56.026 --> 12:57.819
‐ I came to study you.

12:57.819 --> 13:02.032
To‐‐ to study you, in the hopes of‐‐ of...

13:02.032 --> 13:03.534
of becoming you.

13:05.869 --> 13:08.705
And then he‐‐
he might want me back.

13:09.331 --> 13:11.708
‐ Oh.
CARMEL: I'm sorry.

13:11.708 --> 13:15.003
‐ No. I should apologize to you.

13:17.256 --> 13:19.842
I was a different person then, Carmel.

13:21.677 --> 13:26.098
‐ May I ask what was he to you?

13:28.141 --> 13:30.394
‐ You're not gonna like this answer

13:30.394 --> 13:31.520
but he was nothing.

13:31.520 --> 13:32.855
He was a placeholder.

13:32.855 --> 13:34.523
I was consumed with work.

13:34.523 --> 13:36.859
I‐‐ I had affairs with married men

13:36.859 --> 13:39.069
who wouldn't get attached and that was it.

13:41.697 --> 13:44.992
I would never ever hurt you now.

13:46.034 --> 13:48.537
‐ So if you knew my story,
why did you accept me?

13:48.537 --> 13:50.873
‐ I want you to heal.

13:51.498 --> 13:55.586
I want you to get all of this hatred
out of your heart.

13:58.380 --> 14:00.465
I wanna say I'm sorry to you.

14:05.429 --> 14:08.807
Yeah. Yeah. Come, come.

14:09.141 --> 14:10.726
That's right.

14:12.436 --> 14:14.271
Oh, lapochka.

14:14.730 --> 14:16.273
You can trust me.

14:16.815 --> 14:18.442
You're safe with me.

14:20.027 --> 14:21.653
I would never hurt you.

14:21.653 --> 14:23.238
You take the medicine.

14:23.238 --> 14:25.741
‐ I trust you.
‐ Just trust me.

14:25.741 --> 14:26.867
‐ Okay.

15:24.007 --> 15:26.718
YAO: Twist to the right...

15:27.344 --> 15:30.514
Now towards the sun,
and you come down gently.

15:31.056 --> 15:36.770
Just hip level.
Gently come up, keep breathing.

15:38.480 --> 15:41.567
‐ Are you okay?
‐ Hmm. Wobbly.

15:41.567 --> 15:42.860
We have that in common.

15:46.196 --> 15:51.159
Masha, why are you pushing
this protocol so fast?

15:51.577 --> 15:54.872
‐ Because the time is now.
‐ Is it now or never?

15:56.290 --> 15:57.916
What are we, out of money?

15:57.916 --> 15:59.418
‐ We're not out of money.

16:00.377 --> 16:03.297
‐ Well, I‐I know that this lawsuit

16:03.297 --> 16:06.091
was a big‐‐ pretty big drain.

16:06.091 --> 16:07.676
‐ We're not out of money.

16:08.969 --> 16:12.431
DELILAH: [sighs]
I saw you last night, eating sugar.

16:13.223 --> 16:14.391
The cake?

16:15.893 --> 16:17.811
‐ That was you?
‐ Mm.

16:18.437 --> 16:20.189
It was actually kind of sweet.

16:20.856 --> 16:21.940
You actually‐‐

16:22.399 --> 16:24.693
[chuckles] You actually seemed
kind of mortal.

16:24.693 --> 16:26.320
Like the rest of us.

16:26.904 --> 16:28.739
Giving in to temptation.

16:31.867 --> 16:35.037
‐ I was trying to connect
with the little girl within me.

16:37.497 --> 16:39.750
DELILAH: Did you?
‐ Not yet.

17:23.335 --> 17:24.461
‐ Tony.

17:26.505 --> 17:27.923
[echoing]: Tony.

17:30.425 --> 17:31.635
Your buddy.

18:38.452 --> 18:40.287
‐ Oh, Leon.
ZOE: Dad?

18:41.330 --> 18:45.000
‐ Oh. Uh, it just, uh,
erupted out of me, huh?

18:45.000 --> 18:47.044
‐ It's normal, it's‐‐
that's a great thing.

18:47.044 --> 18:50.088
‐ That's not normal.
‐ [clapping hands] Wow. Okay.

18:50.088 --> 18:52.466
Mount St. Napoleon onwards.

18:52.466 --> 18:53.634
‐ You sure you're okay?

18:53.634 --> 18:54.885
NAPOLEON: Oh, perfect. Better than ever.

18:54.885 --> 18:57.513
Wow. Uh, maybe a little water. Yeah.

19:01.767 --> 19:03.685
‐ You're a pretty little thing.

19:12.444 --> 19:14.821
‐ Hey. What are you doing?

19:14.821 --> 19:17.032
Gallivanting off like that
without your buddy?

19:17.699 --> 19:18.659
‐ Sorry.

19:19.701 --> 19:21.995
‐ How's your head?
‐ I don't know.

19:21.995 --> 19:25.457
It's kind of‐‐
it feels like a puffy cloud...

19:25.457 --> 19:26.959
‐ Mm‐hm.
‐ ...little bit, you know,

19:26.959 --> 19:29.962
like a cumulus cloud,
pretty with a chance of rain.

19:35.133 --> 19:37.469
‐ Anyway, you shouldn't
really go off like that

19:37.469 --> 19:38.804
and stuff, you know.

19:39.763 --> 19:41.598
FRANCES: Oh, right.
Because of the buddy system.

19:41.598 --> 19:44.518
‐ Yeah.
‐ We're buddies.

19:46.061 --> 19:47.396
Right? You and me?

19:48.730 --> 19:49.690
‐ Yeah.

19:51.400 --> 19:53.485
‐ ♪ What you want from me ♪

19:55.070 --> 19:56.613
‐ Oh, my God, he's going in.

19:57.447 --> 19:58.907
‐ What?
‐ What?

19:58.907 --> 20:00.659
‐ What'd you say?
‐ I didn't say anything.

20:00.659 --> 20:02.411
‐ You did, you just said,
"Oh my God. He's going in."

20:03.287 --> 20:05.497
‐ Did I say that out loud?
‐ Yeah.

20:06.623 --> 20:08.333
‐ [stammering] I thought it.

20:08.333 --> 20:11.670
I didn't think I said it out loud.

20:11.670 --> 20:14.006
These‐‐ oh, these mushrooms
are like a doozy‐‐

20:14.006 --> 20:15.465
‐ What does that even mean though?

20:15.465 --> 20:17.259
"Oh my God. He's going in."
What does that mean?

20:17.968 --> 20:19.303
‐ You had a‐‐

20:21.054 --> 20:25.184
a look on your face
like you were gonna kiss me.

20:25.184 --> 20:26.101
So...

20:28.061 --> 20:29.396
Were you thinking that?

20:30.147 --> 20:32.065
‐ Yeah, I mean, I was thinking it.

20:34.026 --> 20:34.943
‐ And?

20:36.069 --> 20:37.905
‐ I remembered that
everything I ever touch

20:37.905 --> 20:38.864
I hurt.

20:40.073 --> 20:41.783
Especially the people I love.

20:44.203 --> 20:45.704
I don't wanna do that to you, Frances.

20:45.704 --> 20:46.830
I don't wanna hurt you.

20:46.830 --> 20:48.582
‐ Is that why you didn't kiss me?

20:48.582 --> 20:50.000
‐ That and it would involve leaning

20:50.000 --> 20:51.335
and I don't think
I could do that right now.

20:51.335 --> 20:52.794
I'm pretty dizzy.
I'm afraid I'm gonna fall.

20:52.794 --> 20:54.796
‐ I'll catch you.

20:54.796 --> 20:56.590
God, I've written this scene

20:56.590 --> 20:58.926
like a million times,
I'm sure Paul would say like

20:58.926 --> 21:00.719
it's a very gimmicky scene, but‐‐

21:00.719 --> 21:02.262
‐ Can w just forget
about Paul for a second?

21:02.262 --> 21:03.639
‐ Yup.

21:03.639 --> 21:06.058
‐ Okay.
Full disclosure, I'm a terrible kisser.

21:06.058 --> 21:09.770
‐ So when it is awful‐‐

21:09.770 --> 21:10.938
‐ Just lay it on me.

21:11.688 --> 21:13.232
‐ I'm not gonna make the first move.

21:13.232 --> 21:15.025
‐ I'm gonna make the move.

21:15.025 --> 21:17.152
‐ Are you?
‐ Yeah. Here it comes.

21:17.778 --> 21:20.405
‐ It's kind of funny
you're this big football,

21:20.405 --> 21:22.574
you know, guy.

21:22.574 --> 21:24.368
I mean, he‐‐ like cute‐‐

21:24.368 --> 21:27.871
‐ ♪ Must be love on the brain ♪

21:53.313 --> 21:55.148
‐ You weren't kidding. That was terrible.

21:55.148 --> 21:56.942
‐ Thanks.
[both chuckle]

21:58.193 --> 22:00.028
‐ If that was terrible,
I can't even imagine

22:00.028 --> 22:02.281
what the good one is like.
‐ Oh my God, I'm going in.

22:04.741 --> 22:06.326
[laughs] What are you doing?

22:06.326 --> 22:07.828
You said you were gonna catch me.

22:07.828 --> 22:09.997
‐ I can't catch you,
I have no upper body strength.

22:12.249 --> 22:13.792
‐ How you doing? You feeling okay?

22:13.792 --> 22:15.961
‐ I feel nothing. I can't feel my legs.

22:18.547 --> 22:19.840
Help. [squeaks]

22:31.602 --> 22:32.644
HEATHER: Sweetheart.

22:33.645 --> 22:35.147
You okay?

22:35.147 --> 22:37.191
‐ Yeah, I barely feel anything.

22:38.817 --> 22:41.612
‐ Well, it hits people at different times.

22:44.406 --> 22:46.033
‐ I'm absolutely bonkers.

22:47.701 --> 22:49.536
It's just really
just a matter of perspective.

22:49.536 --> 22:51.246
It's, you know, trick of the mind

22:51.246 --> 22:53.332
because everything
you think you are is a story

22:53.332 --> 22:55.584
you tell yourself about yourself, right?

22:56.960 --> 22:59.838
‐ The vomit was real.
NAPOLEON: Yeah, it was.

23:01.298 --> 23:02.674
‐ I'm gonna go for a walk.

23:03.675 --> 23:06.094
HEATHER: No, I think
we should stick together.

